{"title":"Old Folks Laugh","author":{"name":"Maya Angelou"},"publishDate":"2011-07-14","lines":[{"line":"They have spent their","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"content of simpering,","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"holding their lips this","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"and that way, winding","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"the lines between","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"their brows. Old folks","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"allow their bellies to jiggle like slow","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"tambourines.","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"The hollers","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"rise up and spill","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"over any way they want.","stanza":1,"number":11},{"line":"When old folks laugh, they free the world.","stanza":1,"number":12},{"line":"They turn slowly, slyly knowing","stanza":1,"number":13},{"line":"the best and the worst","stanza":1,"number":14},{"line":"of remembering.","stanza":1,"number":15},{"line":"Saliva glistens in","stanza":1,"number":16},{"line":"the corners of their mouths,","stanza":1,"number":17},{"line":"their heads wobble","stanza":1,"number":18},{"line":"on brittle necks, but","stanza":1,"number":19},{"line":"their laps","stanza":1,"number":20},{"line":"are filled with memories.","stanza":1,"number":21},{"line":"When old folks laugh, they consider the promise","stanza":1,"number":22},{"line":"of dear painless death, and generously","stanza":1,"number":23},{"line":"forgive life for happening","stanza":1,"number":24},{"line":"to them.","stanza":1,"number":25}]}